uk.co.strangeskies.observable

Class PassthroughObserver<T,U>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.strangeskies.observable.PassthroughObserver<T,U>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The message type of the upstream observable
    U - The message type of the downstream observer
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observer<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BackpressureReducingObserver, DropWhileObserver, FilteringObserver, FlatMappingObserver, MappingObserver, MaterializingObserver, ReferenceObserver, ReferenceOwnedObserver, RepeatingObserver, RetryingObserver, SafeObserver, SynchronizedObserver, TakeWhileObserver

    public abstract class PassthroughObserver<T,U>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Observer<T>
    This is a helper class for implementing passive observables.

    A passive observable is one which does not maintain a set of observations or manage its own events, instead deferring to one or more upstream observables. When an observer subscribes to a passive observable, typically the observer is decorated, and the decorator is then subscribed to the parents. This way the decorator can modify, inspect, or filter events as appropriate before passing them back through to the original observer.

    This class is a partial implementation of such a decorator.
